AGI - Israel will respond to the Iranian attack, but it is not clear how and if it will be so violent to transform a spiral of violence into a large-scale regional war.<br> U.S. officials have stated that some form of counterattack to the Iranian attack, which involved more than 300 missiles and drones, is almost inevitable, but the Biden administration still hopes in a limited and uncontrolled counterattack to Iranian territory.
&nbsp;
"This launch of so many missiles, cruise missiles and drones against Israeli territory will receive an answer," said the Chief of Staff of the Israeli defence forces, Lieutenant General Herzi Halevi, speaking from the Nevatim Airbase in southern Israel, which was slightly damaged by the attack.<br> The Israeli war cabinet met for the fourth time in the last two days Monday afternoon, when Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu, his Minister of Defense, Yoav Gallant, and Benny Gantz, former Minister of Defence and centrist rival of Netanyahu, again discussed how to proceed between escalation and deterrence. >
&nbsp;
"We respect that this is a decision that belongs to the cabinet of war, to the Prime Minister," said on Monday to CNN the spokesman for National Security of the White House, John Kirby who added that Joe Biden "was also very clear that Washington does not want a war with Iran >. We are not trying to expand and expand this conflict. We don't want to see the degenerate situation."
&nbsp;
A series of options were discussed during a long-term meeting, reported the Israeli channel N12 News, to show Iran that its actions crossed the red line without triggering an even more violent response.
&nbsp;
N12 reported that Israel intends to coordinate with the United States in its response, but the Biden administration has repeatedly stated that it will not take part in any Israeli counterattack. On Monday, U.S. officials appeared resigned to the fact that the Israeli government would not listen to Biden's advice of "considering a victory" the overthrow of the vast majority of missiles and drones launched in the night between Saturday night and Sunday morning.<br> The IDF claims that they were not even parties. In the end, only four Iranian missiles hit Nevatim.
<br The Biden administration, however, hopes that the counterattack does not physically target something on Iranian soil, but takes the form of a large-scale cyber attack, or targeting an Iranian ally or Iranian military target in a third country such as Lebanon, Syria or Iraq.<br> Another possibility is a secret attack against a goal within Iran not explicitly recognized by Israel and carried out by special forces or secret services of the Jewish state. In recent decades, a series of murders of Iranian nuclear scientists and explosions in sensitive military sites attributed to Israel have occurred, but any open attack on military sites or infrastructural goals within Iran would be seen differently from Tehran making a total war much more likely.

